I had a idea around in the PoFG threads, but it didn't exactly fit that general's main idea so I came here.

The premise was something akin to "Planet of the Furries", where either Earth is a post-apocalyptic mess where furries rule the world and humans have become sub-intelligent species that prowl the wild or are kept in zoos; or that this Earth is an alternate universe where humans didn't fully evolve to the top of the food chain and in their stead furries did.

The story follows the PoV of a furry anthropologist (scientist about humans, think a Dian Fossey expy but with humans instead of gorillas) in a pseudo-Victorian/early-industrialist setting. She is accompanied by her research team and a group of local guides in the search for an elusive group of humans who the locals have reported are behaving very oddly.

Not only is the human pack much more elusive than most other human pack despite having several times the members than other packs, there is a local legend starting to grow about the pack is being led by a strange-looking human much taller and secretive than the others, some suggesting it's a vengeful spirit of nature and such superstitions.

Of course, the elusive human is actually a alternate-reality/past time-space traveler astronaut guy Anon who is stuck in Furryworld until he figures out how to fix his mumbo-jumbo space-time ship, and in the meantime became the leader of the less intelligent humans and has led them to try and keep the furries away from his ship, in the meantime organizing them and teaching them as much as he can, although he is still much more developed than them.

So the research team keep looking for this group of humans, but are eventually attacked by one of their patrols. The local guides abandon the researchers and run away, and the researchers disperse and end up lost int he jungle. Almost all of them make it back to civilization save for the MC researcher and one of her assistants, a furry half-local girl.
